Functions vs Methods
And how to write your own function!
A function is code written to perform a task
Methods are properties containing functions i.e. document.getElementById()
document is the object - the DOM
getElementById() is the function using dot notation to store as property
There are functions that are pre-written for you to use, and you can create your own functions
The functions you create will likely have multiple methods and functions in it
